Noisy independent tables

For each cell entry, a noisy value is sampled from a beta distribution parametrized with \(\alpha = \mu * v\) and \(\beta = (1-\mu) * v\) where \(\mu\) is the respective cell entry. Plot beta distributions for each cell entry of a particular table depending on noise parameter \(v\).

noise_v <- c(10, 50, 100, 500)
table <- c(0.7, 0.1, 0.15, 0.05)

v <- noise_v[[1]]
x <- table %>% map(function(p){
  rbeta(1000, p*v, (1-p)*v) %>% as_tibble()})  %>% bind_rows(.id = "cell") 
## Warning: Calling `as_tibble()` on a vector is discouraged, because the behavior is likely to change in the future. Use `tibble::enframe(name = NULL)` instead.
## This warning is displayed once per session.
means <- x %>% group_by(cell) %>%  summarize(mean=mean(value))

for(v in noise_v){
  x <- table %>% map(function(p){
  rbeta(1000, p*v, (1-p)*v) %>% as_tibble()})  %>% bind_rows(.id = "cell")
  pl <- x %>% ggplot(aes(x=value, color=cell)) +
                      geom_density() +
                      facet_wrap(~cell, scales = "free_y") + 
                      labs(title =  paste("parameter v:", v)) +
                      geom_vline(aes(xintercept=mean), data=means, linetype="dotted",
                      color="red") 
  print(pl)
}

Load tables generated with particular beta/theta from noisy or model: \(P(C|A)=\theta + \beta * \theta - \beta, P(C|\neg A)=\beta\) and \(P(A)\sim beta(1,1)\); or if beta/theta=NA, \(P(C|A)\sim beta(10,1), P(C|\neg A)\sim beta(1,10)\) and \(P(A)\sim beta(1,1)\).

param_theta <- NA
param_beta <- NA

target_dir <- file.path("..", "..", "data", "precomputations", "model-general",
                        sep="")

tables <- read_rds(paste(target_dir,"tables-all.rds",sep=""))
if(is.na(param_theta)){
    tables <- tables %>% filter(is.na(beta) & is.na(theta))
} else {
    tables <- tables %>% filter(beta==param_beta & theta==param_theta)
}
tables_independent <- tables %>% filter(cn=="A || C")

assert(unique(tables_independent$theta) %>% length() == 1)
assert(unique(tables_independent$beta) %>% length() == 1)

Compute mean/median/max/min for indpendence-score p: |P(A,C)-P(A)*P(C)| and also P(C|A), the dependence-score for network A->C.

tables_tidy <- tables %>% select(ps, vs, rowid, noise_v, cn) %>%
                unnest() %>% spread(key=vs, value=ps) %>%
               mutate(C=`AC`+`-AC`, A=`AC`+`A-C`, p=abs(`AC`-(C*A)),
                      p_ac=`AC`/(`AC`+`A-C`)) %>% 
               gather(`AC`, `A-C`, `-AC`, `-A-C`, key="cell", value="val")

tables_wide <- tables_tidy %>%  spread(key=cell, value=val)

means_p <- tables_wide %>% group_by(noise_v, cn) %>%
            summarize(mean_p=mean(p), min_p=min(p), max_p=max(p),
                      median_p=median(p),
                      mean_pac=mean(p_ac), min_pac=min(p_ac), max_pac=max(p_ac),
                      median_pac=median(p_ac))
means_p

Plot distributions of p (independence measure) for different noise parameters \(v\).

Use beta distributions (with different parameters for different noise parameter) to approximate distributions of p (independence measure).

Compute mean squared error between actual and approximated values.

tibbles <- list()
i <- 1
tables_ind <- tables_wide %>% filter(cn=="A || C")
for(noise in noise_vals){
  data <- tables_ind %>% filter(noise_v==noise) %>% pull(p) %>% density()
  t <- tibble(x=data$x, y=data$y, noise_v=noise) %>% filter(x>=0)
  tibbles[[i]] <- t
  i <- i + 1
}
densities_tibble <- bind_rows(tibbles)

df <- densities_tibble %>% group_by(noise_v) %>% 
      mutate(f1=dbeta(x, 1, 25), f2=dbeta(x, 1,30),
             f3=dbeta(x, 1, 35), f4=dbeta(x, 1,50),
             f5=dbeta(x, 1, 70), f6=dbeta(x, 1,110),
             f7=dbeta(x, 1, 150)) %>% 
      gather(f1, f2, f3, f4, f5, f6, f7, key="model", value="val")

df_summary <- df %>% group_by(noise_v, model) %>% summarise(mse=mse(y,val))

Plot the distributions of p (independence measure) and of P(C|A) (dependence measure for network A->C) for all networks.

noise <- 100
mean_vals <- means_p %>% filter(noise_v==noise)

tables_wide %>% filter(noise_v==noise) %>% 
  ggplot() + geom_density(aes(x=p,color=cn)) + facet_wrap(~cn, scales="free") +
  geom_vline(aes(xintercept=mean_p), data=mean_vals, linetype="dashed") +
  geom_vline(aes(xintercept=median_p), data=mean_vals, linetype="dotted",
             color="red") 

tables_wide %>% filter(noise_v==noise) %>% 
  ggplot() + geom_density(aes(x=p_ac, color=cn)) +
  facet_wrap(~cn, scales="free") +
  geom_vline(aes(xintercept=mean_pac), data=mean_vals, linetype="dashed") +
  geom_vline(aes(xintercept=median_pac), data=mean_vals, linetype="dotted",
             color="red")
